cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.FL, cs.DB 

This paper discusses bidirectional transformations (bx) and their implementation using monads to account for effects. This topic falls under the area of programming languages (cs.PL) as it deals with the implementation of bx as functions. The paper also discusses the subtleties of equivalence of symmetric bidirectional transformations, which falls under the area of logic in computer science (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper discusses the obstacles to adding monadic effects to existing definitions of bx, which falls under the area of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the use of lenses, which is a topic in formal languages (cs.FL), and the use of databases (cs.DB) to store and manipulate bidirectional transformations.
